item.title: Running Extracted RS Client
item.dc:creator: @yakman yakman
item.description:
@yakman wrote:

as frank_ said, you have to edit it to connect to something else

if you’re starting it through main() and its a deob, look for the string “127.0.0.1” and change that to the server, like “jolt1.runescape.com” or something

if you’re using a bytecode editor, change the ldc that pushes “127.0.0.1”

if you’re using bcel, im not really sure, but i guess you change the ldc instruction, or change to invokestatic your own method

with the worldid, it does things like decide what it says on the friends list, but the server decides the color (green or yellow)
so you can be on the same world as someone, but make the text yellow
a lot of people iv seen just put it to world 1
